			<description><![CDATA[Monica:  Om shanti.  Creative people are often sensitive.  Sensitivity is a good thing when it means we can catch the subtle aspects of spiritual wisdom.  Meditation helps to develop this spiritual sensitivity and emerges the wisdom from within the soul.  Meditation also helps us to protect ourselves from negative vibrations, be they from ourselves, a situation, or another person, when we keep practicing this, as with any practice, we become more accomplished.  As we spend time with ourselves in meditation we begin to know and trust ourselves and recognize that we are a unique and powerful soul, a child of God, and as such have the power of truth, love, peace, and purity within.  By connecting in meditation with God, the Supreme Soul, our spiritual parent, we can also access God's imperishable qualities.  As we know and trust ourselves more we will understand and trust others also. In this way our spiritual influence too spreads and this gives strength to others.  Our mothers are indeed special and have a lot of love for us.  With patience it is good to encourage any of our companions not to gossip - as this is a waste of time and energy and also causes harm to ourselves and others - as we spread this negativity into the atmosphere.  By listening to gossip we are actually encouraging the other and so we have to pay attention not to do this.]]></description>
