			<description><![CDATA[Samita:  True love has no expectation but loves the person as they are.  Attachment on the other hand causes a lot of sorrow when the object of that attachment disappoints us.  The first step to forgiveness is to step back from the situation and as a detached observer understand from a spiritual perspective, and decide how to respond in a way that will bring benefit to all concerned, including yourself.  Each soul has their own part to play in this drama of life and every action we choose to do have its consequences - the best way to forgive is to let go of the past and understand what we want to create for the future.  Relying on others for your happiness and functioning in this world will inevitably bring sorrow.  God is the Ocean of Love, Forgiveness, and Mercy, draw power from Him in meditation and you will bring strength into your life and through this, bring strength to those who are in connection with you.]]></description>
